<p>San Diego's Mediterranean climate makes it one of the premier locations for solar energy in the United States. With over 260 sunny days per year and minimal seasonal weather variation, homeowners in this city of 1.4 million residents can maximize their solar investment year-round. The consistent sunshine, combined with San Diego Gas & Electric's (SDG&E) high electricity rates of 32.4¬¢ per kilowatt-hour, creates compelling financial incentives for solar adoption across San Diego County.</p>

